      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Invisible losses, especially with small, high-value items, often point to sophisticated methods or systemic failures rather than obvious theft. Consider potential internal collusion or \"ghost inventory\" entries, where items are digitally removed but not physically accounted for. Also, check for environmental factors like damage during transit within the warehouse that might be misclassified as shrinkage. Sometimes, weak supplier packaging or poor staging areas can lead to items being lost before they even hit the main stockroom.",
